Certain champs don't give two-shits about windwall {{champion:122}} {{champion:101}} {{champion:114}} {{champion:120}} {{champion:59}} {{champion:78}} {{champion:48}} {{champion:83}} {{champion:154}} and my personal favorite against Yasuo {{champion:58}} 

I get Yasuo is annoying because Windwall does stop A LOT of champion's abilities but it also has a long cd and there are quite a few champions that it can't stop. 

For mid lane I've always found it easy to go up against a Yasuo as Xerath as windwall doesn't even block Xerath's Q it still pierces and full damage. The only thing you have to watch for in that match up is a gank from the jg.  Yasuo is annoying but too many people want to act like he has no counter. Hell when you get Rylai on Xerath it's pretty much game over for Yasuo because he can't do anything about your W and the slow from Rylai's makes it super easy to land your ult and just delete him. A lot of the other champs I showed do quick work against Yasuo as well, especially Renekton.

> her rockets should not be &quot;i crit one, the rest also get crit&quot;

Are you suggesting that crit gets calculated for each target affected? Because that would not only be a lot more work on Riot's end, but it would also have zero impact on her DPS.

The better option would be to have Rockets only apply crit to the target hit, and the AoE explosion to be considered a physical damage spell that either scales with pure AD, or a mixture of AD and crit chance.
